---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Christopher Badgett — cybersecurity student, homelab builder, and 3D printing hobbyist."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-bg-surface border-b border-border">
    <div class="container py-16 sm:py-20">
      <p class="section-label">// about me</p>
      <h1 class="section-title text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Christopher Badgett</h1>
      <p class="font-mono text-text-muted text-lg mt-3">@cmbadgett</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container py-16">
    <div class="mb-10 bg-bg-card border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg px-5 py-4 flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="text-yellow-400 font-mono shrink-0 mt-0.5">⚠</span>
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400 font-semibold mb-1">// work in progress</p>
        <p class="font-sans text-sm text-text-muted">This page is still being filled out — some sections are placeholders and may not reflect current details.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-16">
      <!-- Main content -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-12">
        <!-- Bio -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-mono text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-cyan">//</span> The short version
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-sans leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              I'm a cybersecurity student who got tired of reading about networking and decided
              to just build it instead. My homelab started as a single Raspberry Pi running
              Pi-hole and has since grown into a full rack: a 72 TB NAS, a four-node Kubernetes
              cluster, a managed switch, a dedicated firewall, and more cables than I care to count.
            </p>
            <p>
              On the security side, I spend time doing CTF competitions, studying for certifications,
              and writing tools that make the tedious parts of recon and analysis faster. Most of that
              tooling lives on GitHub — rough around the edges, but it does the job.
            </p>
            <p>
              The 3D printing hobby started as a way to make enclosures for the homelab hardware
              and quickly became its own rabbit hole. I'm currently running a Bambu Lab P1S for FDM
              and an Elegoo Saturn 4 Ultra for resin prints. If it fits on the build plate and
              someone in my house will use it, it's fair game.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Currently -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-mono text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-cyan">//</span> Currently
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              { icon: '📚', text: 'Studying for CompTIA Security+ (exam booked for Q3)' },
              { icon: '🖥️', text: 'Migrating homelab workloads from Docker Compose to K3s' },
              { icon: '🔒', text: 'Competing in weekly CTF challenges on HackTheBox and TryHackMe' },
              { icon: '🖨️', text: 'Designing a full custom rack-mount enclosure in Fusion 360' },
              { icon: '📡', text: 'Setting up WireGuard-based split-tunnel VPN for remote lab access' },
            ].map(({ icon, text }) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-text-muted font-sans">
                <span class="mt-0.5 text-base">{icon}</span>
                <span>{text}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Interests -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-mono text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-cyan">//</span> What I actually care about
          </h2>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            {[
              {
                title: 'Network Security',
                desc: 'Subnetting, firewall rules, intrusion detection — the fundamentals that underpin everything else.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Self-Hosting',
                desc: "If there's a service I use regularly and a self-hosted alternative exists, I've probably tried it.",
              },
              {
                title: 'Hardware & Bare Metal',
                desc: 'There\'s something satisfying about knowing exactly what\'s running on what, and why.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Open Source',
                desc: 'I believe in owning your stack. Most of what I run is open source, and I try to contribute back.',
              },
            ].map(({ title, desc }) => (
              <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
                <h3 class="font-mono font-semibold text-text-primary text-sm mb-2">{title}</h3>
                <p class="text-text-muted text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">{desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Profile image placeholder -->
        <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden aspect-square flex items-center justify-center">
          <div class="text-center p-8">
            <div class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full bg-accent-cyan/10 border-2 border-accent-cyan/30 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-accent-cyan text-3xl font-bold">CB</span>
            </div>
            <p class="font-mono text-text-muted text-xs">[ photo coming soon ]</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick facts -->
        <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">
            <span class="text-accent-cyan">$</span> cat facts.txt
          </h3>
          <dl class="space-y-3">
            {[
              { label: 'Location',    value: 'United States' },
              { label: 'Education',   value: 'B.S. Cybersecurity & Networks' },
              { label: 'Class of',    value: '2026'          },
              { label: 'Certs',       value: 'CompTIA A+'    },
              { label: 'Primary OS',  value: 'Arch btw'      },
              { label: 'Editor',      value: 'Neovim'        },
              { label: 'Shell',       value: 'Zsh + Starship' },
            ].map(({ label, value }) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between gap-2 text-xs font-mono">
                <dt class="text-text-muted">{label}</dt>
                <dd class="text-text-primary text-right">{value}</dd>
              </div>
            ))}
          </dl>
        </div>

        <!-- Skills -->
        <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">
            <span class="text-accent-cyan">$</span> skills --list
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { category: 'Languages',  items: ['Python', 'Bash', 'Go', 'TypeScript'] },
              { category: 'Security',   items: ['Nmap', 'Burp Suite', 'Wireshark', 'Metasploit', 'Ghidra'] },
              { category: 'Infra',      items: ['Linux', 'Docker', 'Kubernetes', 'Ansible', 'Terraform'] },
              { category: 'Networking', items: ['TCP/IP', 'VLAN', 'BGP (lab)', 'WireGuard', 'pfSense'] },
            ].map(({ category, items }) => (
              <div>
                <p class="text-text-muted text-xs mb-2">{category}</p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
                  {items.map(item => <span class="tag">{item}</span>)}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Links -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <a href="https://github.com/cmbadgett" class="btn-outline w-full justify-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
              <path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"/>
            </svg>
            GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopher-badgett-b59a86286/" class="btn-ghost w-full justify-center border border-border hover:border-border-bright" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
              <path d="M20.447 20.452h-3.554v-5.569c0-1.328-.027-3.037-1.852-3.037-1.853 0-2.136 1.445-2.136 2.939v5.667H9.351V9h3.414v1.561h.046c.477-.9 1.637-1.85 3.37-1.85 3.601 0 4.267 2.37 4.267 5.455v6.286zM5.337 7.433a2.062 2.062 0 01-2.063-2.065 2.064 2.064 0 112.063 2.065zm1.782 13.019H3.555V9h3.564v11.452zM22.225 0H1.771C.792 0 0 .774 0 1.729v20.542C0 23.227.792 24 1.771 24h20.451C23.2 24 24 23.227 24 22.271V1.729C24 .774 23.2 0 22.222 0h.003z"/>
            </svg>
            LinkedIn
          </a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary w-full justify-center">
            Get in Touch
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
